name: purse seiner construction, steel | purse seiner, steel | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/18944/documentation

This dataset represents the construction of steel purse seiners, per 1000 kg of light ship weight, based on data from Peru and Ecuador, corresponding to 143+12 vessels for which data was avilable with different levels of detail. Specific data for specific inventory items may be based on sub-samples for which detailed data was available. Vessel dimensions, landings and fuel use were available for roughly 661 purse seiners.;System boundaries and relation between activities

Construction of vessels, including provision of all materials and work

Batteries are excluded, as they do not exist in the database
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/03:Fishing and aquaculture/031:Fishing/0311:Marine fishing

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from Peru and Ecuador, extrapolated to global (GLO)
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Peru features various shipyards and relevant ship-building and ship-retrofitting expertise.

exchanges.description: Construction of a steel purse seiner, per 1000 kg of light ship weight (LSW). Regressions based on mainly primary data were created to relate the weight of each inventory item to a purse seiner's LSW. The list of inventory items (granularity) contribute >95% of environmental impacts, as described in the reference publication.
